{
  "text": "Planorotalites capdevilensis is quite abundant in both the Tethyan sections investigated. At Alano (0.6-0.8 km palaeodepth), in most samples it is less abundant than at the M. Cagnero section (palaeodepth c. 1-2 km), but it is more abundant in the samples above the sapropelic intervals. However, different sedimentation rates at the Alano and M. Cagnero sections do not allow comparisons of absolute abundances of P. capdevilensis between the sections [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
